The paper discusses techniques for creating cross-referenced parallel MathML, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a likely category since the paper discusses enhanced search indexing. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely categories since the paper discusses interaction with parts of the presentation to manipulate and querying the corresponding content, which could be relevant to natural language processing and machine learning. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category since the paper discusses heuristics and decision-making. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category since the paper discusses search indexing and querying.
